The paper proposes a task and motion planning algorithm for robots in human social environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm also considers social context, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions strategies to limit complexity, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) or machine learning (cs.MA).
